File: Face masks. AFP/Thomas Kienzle JOHANNESBURG - The bail application for the remaining 12 people accused of PPE corruption will resume on Monday at the Palm Ridge Magistrates court. Three people were granted bail on Tuesday. 15 people in total were arrested for corruption, involving the procurement of personal protective equipment, worth R1.9 million in the South African Police Service. READ: SAPS PPE corruption | 15 suspects to appear in court Six of the accused are former police officers. They claim there is a vendetta against them. They allege that the NPA is reviving previous cases to deal with them.